{"type":"message","id":"52294202","parentId":"8075984e","timestamp":"2026-03-22T13:00:30.564Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the sizes match almost exactly what Zach said:\n- playground.ts: 15KB ✓\n- schema-routes.ts: 17KB ✓\n- world-state.ts: 9KB (Zach said 8.7KB, close enough)\n- mcp-server/index.ts: 15KB ✓\n\nNow I need to create a comprehensive PLAN.md based on Zach's detailed analysis. Let me write it to the schemocker-tmp directory and also create a copy in the workspace memory.\n\nThe plan should integrate Zach's suggestions:\n1. `src/mcp-server/index.ts` - Add `generate_schema_from_nl` MCP tool\n\n\n2. `src/generators/schema-routes.ts` - Add LLM-backed field enricher with `--ai-enrich` flag\n3. `src/generators/world-state.ts` - Schema-description-driven state mutation logic\n4. `src/generators/playground.ts` - Schema chat interface\n5. `src/cli/` - Add `schemock infer <description>` command\n6. `src/integrations/` - Add OpenAI/Anthropic/Ollama provider adapter layer\n7. New `src/ai/` module for provider abstraction, schema inference, and field enrichment\n\nI'm also looking at the `schemock.json` config to understand the current structure.","thinkingSignature":"83765e1da26f1eadc1b293cc4e41538048f22502209a73fd9f43f8eea25138c4"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_agz5omqxfrx2_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\schemocker-tmp\\schemock.json"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":13549,"output":313,"cacheRead":12333,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26195,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774184422543}}
