{"type":"message","id":"0a4ec6cf","parentId":"09982295","timestamp":"2026-03-22T13:02:01.646Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK, so I have all the data I need. Now let me write the PLAN.md. I'll create it based on Zach's detailed analysis, integrating his suggestions with the actual codebase structure.\n\nThe plan should be comprehensive and cover:\n1. Vision - AI-native mock API generation\n2. Architecture changes (new `src/ai/` module)\n3. Implementation order (prioritized)\n4. File-by-file changes\n5. Config expansion\n6. CLI additions\n\nLet me write the plan now and save it both to the cloned repo (for Zach to use) and to workspace memory.","thinkingSignature":"19309c0c9c3bc523e8f43d3931692478682fc00ab78f0742753ccc1aa1211416"},{"type":"text","text":"Good — verified all the sizes match. Now writing the plan:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_12erdv7xe1ww_1","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Schemocker AI-Native Evolution Plan\n\n> **Goal:** Transform Schemocker from a passive mock API server into an **AI-native API co-authoring tool** — where the AI doesn't just consume your schema, it helps build it and generates intelligent mock data that understands semantics, not just formats.\n\n---\n\n## Current State\n\n| File | Size | Role |\n|---|---|---|\n| `src/server.ts` | 19KB | Core HTTP server |\n| `src/mcp-server/index.ts` | 15KB | MCP tooling (passive) |\n| `src/generators/schema-routes.ts` | 17KB | Faker-based data gen |\n| `src/generators/world-state.ts` | 9KB | In-memory state (static) |\n| `src/playground.ts` | 15KB | Interactive UI shell |\n| `src/cli/` | — | Command flags only |\n\n**Core gap:** Zero AI layer. All data is format-matched faker output. The MCP server exposes tools but doesn't generate anything.\n\n---\n\n## New Module: `src/ai/`\n\nA dedicated, zero-dep-by-default AI layer. Isolates all LLM dependencies behind an interface — binary users who don't want AI features pay zero cost.\n\n```\nsrc/ai/\n├── provider.ts          # Abstract adapter: OpenAI / Anthropic / Ollama / vLLM\n├── schema-inferrer.ts   # NL description → JSON Schema pipeline\n├── field-enricher.ts    # Semantic field value generator\n└── state-advisor.ts     # Reads description fields → infers valid mutations\n```\n\n### `provider.ts` — Provider Abstraction\n\n```typescript\nexport type AIProvider = 'openai' | 'anthropic' | 'ollama' | 'vllm';\n\nexport interface AIConfig {\n  provider: AIProvider;\n  model: string;\n  baseUrl?: string;        // For Ollama/vLLM self-hosted\n  apiKey?: string;         // For OpenAI/Anthropic cloud\n  maxTokens?: number;\n  temperature?: number;\n}\n\nexport interface AIResponse {\n  content: string;\n  usage?: { promptTokens: number; completionTokens: number };\n}\n\nexport abstract class AIProviderAdapter {\n  abstract complete(prompt: string, config: AIConfig): Promise<AIResponse>;\n}\n\n// Implementations: OpenAIAdapter, AnthropicAdapter, OllamaAdapter, VLLMAdapter\n```\n\n**Key design:** The adapter is injectable. If `--ai-provider` is not set, the entire `src/ai/` module is tree-shaken out for users who don't need it.\n\n### `schema-inferrer.ts` — NL → JSON Schema\n\n```typescript\n// schemock infer \"a blog post with title, author, tags, and published date\"\n// → returns a valid JSON Schema\n\nexport async function inferSchema(nlDescription: string, config: AIConfig): Promise< object> {\n  const prompt = buildInferPrompt(nlDescription);\n  const response = await complete(prompt, config);\n  return JSON.parse(response.content);\n}\n```\n\nThe prompt should be in `src/ai/prompts/schema-inferrer.ts` as a separate template file (keeps prompts editable without touching logic).\n\n### `field-enricher.ts` — Smart Fake Values\n\n```typescript\n// When --ai-enrich is set, semantic fields get contextually appropriate content\n// Instead of: { \"bio\": \"John Doe\" }  (faker default)\n// We get:      { \"bio\": \"ML researcher focused on efficient inference and sparse architectures\" }\n\nexport async function enrichField(\n  fieldName: string,\n  fieldSchema: JSONSchema,\n  config: AIConfig\n): Promise<unknown>\n```\n\nField name + schema description are used as context. Call a small local model (Qwen2.5-3B via Ollama) — latency should be <100ms for single fields, <2s for full object.\n\n**Trigger logic:**\n- Field name matches enrichment list (from `schemock.json` `ai.enrich` array, e.g. `[\"description\", \"bio\", \"comment\", \"content\"]`)\n- OR field has a `description` in the schema\n- Falls back to faker if AI call fails\n\n### `state-advisor.ts` — Mutation Intelligence\n\nReads `description` fields from POST/PUT/PATCH request schemas and infers valid state transitions:\n\n```typescript\n// Schema:\n// { \"productId\": { \"type\": \"string\" }, \"quantity\": { \"type\": \"integer\", \"description\": \" decrements inventory\" } }\n\nexport function inferMutations(schema: JSONSchema): MutationRule[] {\n// → \"when quantity increases, decrement inventory for productId\"\n// → registers a world-state mutation hook\n}\n```\n\nMutation hooks live in `src/generators/world-state.ts` and are applied on write operations. Rules are lightweight — no full rules engine needed at first.\n\n---\n\n## File-by-File Changes\n\n### 1. `src/mcp-server/index.ts` — Generative MCP\n\n**Current:** Exposes schema endpoints as tools for AI to call.\n\n**Change:** Add `generate_schema_from_nl` tool that calls the schema inferrer and hot-reloads the running server.\n\n```typescript\n// New MCP tool\nserver.setRequestHandler(CallToolRequestSchema, async (request) => {\n  switch (request.params.name) {\n    case 'generate_schema_from_nl': {\n      const { description, baseUrl } = request.params.arguments;\n      const schema = await inferSchema(description, resolveAIConfig());\n      await hotReloadSchema(schema);\n      return { content: [{ type: 'text', text: JSON.stringify(schema, null, 2) }] };\n    }\n    // ... existing tools\n  }\n});\n```\n\nAlso add `enrich_mock_data` tool — takes a partial object and field names, returns AI-enriched values.\n\n### 2. `src/generators/schema-routes.ts` — LLM-Backed Field Enricher\n\n**Current:** Faker-style generation based on format matching (UUID → UUID, email → email).\n\n**Change:** After faker runs, pass semantically meaningful fields through `field-enricher.ts`.\n\n```typescript\n// In generateForProperty():\nif (config.aiEnrich && isSemanticField(fieldName, fieldSchema)) {\n  return await enrichField(fieldName, fieldSchema, config);\n}\n```\n\nThe `--ai-enrich` flag gates this. Zero-deps path is unchanged for users without AI configured.\n\n### 3. `src/generators/world-state.ts` — Stateful Mutations\n\n**Current:** GET returns generated snapshot. POST/PUT/PATCH exist but mutate state without logic.\n\n**Change:** Add `MutationEngine` that reads schema `description` fields and registers causal mutation rules.\n\n```typescript\nclass MutationEngine {\n  private rules: MutationRule[] = [];\n\n  registerRulesFromSchema(schema: JSONSchema) {\n    // Parse description fields for mutation hints\n    // e.g. \"decrements inventory\" → decrement rule on that field\n  }\n\n  apply(resource: string, operation: 'POST' | 'PUT' | 'PATCH', data: object): object {\n    // Apply all matching rules, return mutated world state\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 4. `src/generators/playground.ts` — Schema Chat Interface\n\n**Current:** Interactive UI shell (15KB).\n\n**Change:** Add a streaming SSE endpoint and embedded prompt box:\n\n```typescript\n// New endpoint: GET /playground/chat\n// SSE stream for AI responses\n\n// POST /playground/chat\n// { \"prompt\": \"add a notifications array to this schema\" }\n// → AI merges the change into the live schema, streams diff back\n```\n\nPrompt-to-diff flow:\n1. Dev types in playground chat box\n2. Frontend POSTs to `/playground/chat` with current schema + prompt\n3. Backend calls schema inferrer, gets merged schema\n4. SSE streams the diff back as JSON patch\n5. Frontend applies patch and hot-reloads preview\n\n### 5. `src/cli/` — `schemock infer` Command\n\n**Current:** `schemock start`, `schemock validate`, `schemock init`.\n\n**Add:**\n```bash\nschemock infer \"a todo app with users, lists, and items\"\n# → outputs schema.json to stdout or --output <file>\n\nschemock infer --interactive\n# → opens a prompt loop for iterative schema building\n```\n\nImplementation: `src/cli/commands/infer.ts`. Uses `schema-inferrer.ts`.\n\n### 6. `src/integrations/` — AI Provider Adapters\n\n**Current:** Placeholder for future integrations.\n\n**Change:** Implement the `AIProviderAdapter` hierarchy here:\n\n```\nsrc/integrations/ai/\n├── openai-adapter.ts\n├── anthropic-adapter.ts\n├── ollama-adapter.ts\n└── vllm-adapter.ts     # Uses your own A5000 inference stack — showcase for CAAE/EXP\n```\n\n---\n\n## Config Expansion: `schemock.json`\n\n```json\n{\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"ai\": {\n    \"provider\": \"ollama\",\n    \"model\": \"qwen2.5:3b\",\n    \"baseUrl\": \"http://localhost:11434\",\n    \"enrich\": [\"description\", \"bio\", \"comment\", \"content\", \"body\", \"summary\"],\n    \"maxTokens\": 512,\n    \"temperature\": 0.7\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior:**\n- `provider` defaults to `\"ollama\"` if not set (zero-friction local AI)\n- `enrich` array maps field names → always AI-enrich when field name contains any of these substrings (case-insensitive)\n- Falls back to faker if Ollama isn't running\n\n---\n\n## Priority Order\n\n| # | Area | Impact | Effort | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | `src/ai/provider.ts` | Foundation for all AI features | Low | Just interface + 4 adapters |\n| 2 | `schemock.json` AI block | Zero-friction opt-in config | Trivial | 10 lines |\n| 3 | `src/cli/infer.ts` | New command, high user value | Medium | New file, needs schema inferrer |\n| 4 | `src/mcp-server/index.ts` — `generate_schema_from_nl` | MCP becomes generative | Medium | 50-80 lines |\n| 5 | `src/generators/schema-routes.ts` — enricher | Better data, no new UX | Low | Gate behind `--ai-enrich` |\n| 6 | `src/generators/world-state.ts` — MutationEngine | Stateful realism | High | Most complex |\n| 7 | `src/generators/playground.ts` — chat | AI co-authoring UI | High | SSE + frontend |\n| 8 | `src/ai/schema-inferrer.ts` | Used by infer + playground + MCP | Medium | Needs good prompts |\n| 9 | `src/ai/field-enricher.ts` | Semantic data quality | Low | Depends on provider.ts |\n| 10 | `src/ai/state-advisor.ts` | Infers world-state rules | Medium | Parses descriptions |\n| 11 | `src/integrations/ai/` adapters | vLLM = showcase for Zach's infra | Medium | vLLM adapter = CAAE/EXP demo |\n\n---\n\n## The vLLM Angle\n\nThe `vllm` provider adapter is a first-class showcase for Zach's inference stack (EXP/CAAE on Paperspace A5000):\n\n```bash\nschemock infer \"user auth service\" --ai-provider vllm --ai-model qwen3.5-35b-a3b\n```\n\nThis turns Schemocker into a **demo vehicle** for the gateway project — it uses your own inference infrastructure as the AI backend. Point it at `http://<paperspace-endpoint>:8000/v1/chat/completions` and Qwen3.5-35B handles all AI tasks.\n\n---\n\n## Files to Create / Modify\n\n```\nsrc/ai/\n+ provider.ts           [NEW]\n+ schema-inferrer.ts    [NEW]\n+ field-enricher.ts     [NEW]\n+ state-advisor.ts      [NEW]\n+ prompts/\n+   schema-inferrer.ts  [NEW]\n\nsrc/cli/commands/\n+ infer.ts              [NEW]\n\nsrc/integrations/ai/\n+ openai-adapter.ts     [NEW]\n+ anthropic-adapter.ts  [NEW]\n+ ollama-adapter.ts     [NEW]\n+ vllm-adapter.ts       [NEW]\n\nsrc/generators/\n~ schema-routes.ts      [MODIFY — add enricher hook]\n~ world-state.ts        [MODIFY — add MutationEngine]\n\nsrc/mcp-server/\n~ index.ts             [MODIFY — add NL schema tool]\n\nsrc/generators/\n~ playground.ts         [MODIFY — add SSE chat endpoint]\n\nschemock.json           [MODIFY — add ai: block]\n\nsrc/config.example.json [MODIFY — add ai: example]\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n- `src/ai/provider.ts` — mock adapter for unit tests (never hits real API)\n- `src/ai/schema-inferrer.ts` — golden output tests with known NL → schema pairs\n- `src/ai/field-enricher.ts` — snapshot tests for enrichment quality\n- `src/generators/world-state.ts` — mutation rule tests: apply POST → verify state diff\n- MCP tool tests — call `generate_schema_from_nl` with known prompts, verify valid schema returned\n\n---\n\n## Rollout Safety\n\n- `--ai-enrich` flag defaults to `false` — existing users see zero change\n- All AI calls have 5s timeout with faker fallback\n- `schemock.json` `ai:` block is ignored if file is old schema format (backward compat)\n- Binary build excludes `src/ai/` when `AI_FEATURES=0` build tag set\n\n---\n\n*Plan version: 1.0 | Based on architecture analysis 2026-03-22*\n","file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\schemocker-tmp\\PLAN.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":14272,"output":3120,"cacheRead":12333,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29725,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774184436929}}
