{"type":"message","id":"6e43f8ec","parentId":"85ace2de","timestamp":"2026-03-22T13:02:10.760Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me also save this to the workspace memory so it's persistent, and let Zach know it's done.","thinkingSignature":"b3ba05ac7d22d78881e092f2b004c1abc7c29db81ec985a8572ffe347fa8fe28"},{"type":"text","text":"Done. Saved to `C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\schemocker-tmp\\PLAN.md` — the repo is cloned there if you want to work on it directly. Here's what the plan covers:\n\n**New `src/ai/` module** — isolated, zero-dep-by-default, with provider abstraction for OpenAI / Anthropic / Ollama / **vLLM** (your own A5000 stack). vLLM adapter turns Schemocker into a live demo vehicle for the gateway project.\n\n**Priority path:**\n1. `provider.ts` + `schemock.json` AI block (foundation, 30 min)\n2. `schemock infer` CLI command (new user-facing entry point)\n3. `generate_schema_from_nl` MCP tool (makes MCP generative, not just consumptive)\n4. `--ai-enrich` flag for semantic field values\n5. `MutationEngine` in world-state (stateful realism)\n6. Playground SSE chat (AI co-authoring UI)\n\nThe vLLM angle is the most important strategic move — it makes Schemocker a showcase for CAAE/EXP while being genuinely useful on its own. Want me to start scaffolding `src/ai/`?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":17429,"output":274,"cacheRead":12333,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30036,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774184521686}}
