{"type":"message","id":"db96cfb6","parentId":"3538332c","timestamp":"2026-03-22T13:25:01.179Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the MCP server. I need to add the 3 new tools:\n1. `generate_schema` — takes NL description, returns valid JSON Schema, hot-reloads running server\n2. `mutate_schema` — takes current schema + NL instruction, returns merged updated schema\n3. `seed_world` — populate N realistic records using LLM-generated values\n\nI also need to handle the `scenario` parameter in `call_endpoint`.\n\nFor hot-reloading the schema, the MCP server currently calls `POST /__schemock/reload`. I'll need to add a way to accept a new schema inline. Let me add a `POST /__schemock/schema` endpoint for pushing schemas directly, or use the reload endpoint.\n\n\nI'll extend the reload endpoint to accept an inline schema body as well. For `seed_world`, I need to make a `POST /__schemock/seed` endpoint. Looking at the MCP server more carefully, it makes HTTP calls to the running Schemocker server using axios. For `generate_schema` and `mutate_schema`, I'll use the AI provider directly to infer the schema rather than making HTTP calls, then push it to the reload endpoint with the new schema body. The `seed_world` tool will make a POST request to a new seed endpoint that handles population.\n\nNow I'm planning the implementation: add `generate_schema`, `mutate_schema`, and `seed_world` tools to the MCP server, extend `call_endpoint` with a scenario parameter, and have the AI tools use the AI provider directly. The server-side endpoints already exist (`POST /__schemock/reload` and `GET /__schemock/world`), so I just need to add the seed endpoint and modify the reload endpoint to accept an inline schema body. I'm realizing I should leverage the existing server infrastructure instead of building it into the MCP server itself. I'll add the three new tools to the MCP server and update the existing reload endpoint to accept an inline schema body, while also creating the seed endpoint to populate the world with mock data.","thinkingSignature":"3e75360c2ec0646a66b8b78c77be21e3917238a87e8d996b3d6dd07b05928582"},{"type":"text","text":"Now the updated MCP server — 3 new tools + `scenario` param on `call_endpoint`:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_mqzpsdi6h35m_1","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\schemocker-tmp\\src\\server.ts","limit":50}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":29195,"output":495,"cacheRead":12333,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42023,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774185888742}}
