isters each generated item before returning the updated snapshot.\n\nFor the MCP server's `generate_schema` tool, I need to wire it up to call the AI provider which I'll initialize with config derived from environment variables and the request arguments. The tricky part is handling the hot-reload since the MCP server is a client that makes HTTP calls to the running Schemocker server, so I can't directly mutate the schema. Instead, I'll generate the schema via the AI provider, then use the reload endpoint to push it to the server. Now I'm working through the full implementation, starting with the `generate_schema` tool that will handle natural language input, call the AI to generate the schema, and reload it on the server.\n\nFor the hot-reload flow, the MCP server calls `POST /__schemock/reload` with the new schema, and the server reads it, rebuilds its route configuration, and calls `this.restart()` with the updated config. The MCP server also needs to send the current schema to `mutate_schema` since it has to know the existing structure to modify it—the `world_snapshot` tool already retrieves the current schema from the running server.","thinkingSignature":"9d3b1da6b4b5adb834ca622135579d85ff327ff594f9104dc3c5ea949c3442d9"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_38r2p33fq0iq_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Select-String -Path \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\schemocker-tmp\\src\\generators\\server.ts\" -Pattern \"import|require\" | Select-Object LineNumber,Line | Format-Table -AutoSize"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":39641,"output":726,"cacheRead":12333,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":52700,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774186006734}}
